column5: Here's the deal, I'm looking for a some back lakes within 3 hours of Barrie , lakes with camp sites are preferred . I'm finding that with two kids and a wife back in university I have zero time for exploring/testing new waters. I have some OFC street credit with a few members in regards to back lake fishing LOL. In return I'll see if I can accommodate any back lakes info your searching for, within the same area. As for quality, I'm not looking  for your platinum lakes, we can start trading at the Bronze level LOL. If anyone is interested in sharing some info let me know. Cheers Ryan
That would be Quite the offer guys,well worth your input for a good return!!
Damn, wish I had something to offer up!
me too  I can offer you Misfish and a foreign player to be named later  oh wait that's not what you want...lol wish I had some
Any Species" N Partik Q Ler" ??
I got some great places except for the 2 hour limit. If you expand it to 12 we can talk. Best of luck.   Art
Boat, canoe or shore?  What's yer mode of attack?
I have tons but you need an 8 hour limit, and a pickup truck that you don't mind laying a beating on
I'm game, I'm just not sure who owns the boats that I use
Do you take a small motor with you? And is this what the op is doing?  For the record I'm fine with that (respecting a cached boat  for a day)

Boat?  Truck camping or water access?  Size of lake?  How rough of a road are you willing to drive down?  I could point you in the direction of some good ones that are likely just over your 3 hour cap.
Joeys lakes are good.   Might cost you a leaf spring to get in and back though.   It did me.
Hahaha, I gotta get some scratches on the new truck somewhere
Hahaha, Brian's sampled one lake already., cost him an hour or two labour setting up bear baits .   Never free bees. Was worth the slugg,n. Just wish we could get back up to it. Stupid road and car.
hey Ryan. i have been doin back woods trips for yrs from bancroft to temagami area. What r looking to fish for and whats ur boat,truck,quad, or how u getting there
Thanks for all the replies and pms . Hope I got back to everyone, if not let me know. Ryan
I have to say that if you go fishing or hunting with this fella,you better be wearing your Nikes.   This guy is a walking,bush wacking machine.  Hope ya get some good exchanges Ry.
